* ## Month 1 Goals

  - Spend an hour each morning reading the news and not worrying about code
  - Learn how to integrate jQuery and AJAX into web applications
  - Study Ruby syntax to avoid having to go through documentation for typical tasks
  - Spend three to four hours each weekend on leisure
  - Spend four hours each week on the Cloud Guru AWS lessons
  - Prepare and bring a healthy lunch to Turing everyday of the weekend
  - Apply to at least one job per week
  - Reach out to three cold connections each week

### Strategy To Achieve Goals:
#### Coding:

  - Complete a functional, consumer grade web application as part of the personal project for Mod 3
  - Deploy that web application to AWS using Chef or Capistrano
  - Refresh Ruby skills
  - Study non-relational database design and how Ruby uses it
  - Complete a JS and jQuery lessons online
  - Study linux environment and commands

#### Professional Development/Network:

  - Reach out to 2-3 people using cold outreach techniques
  - Identify 1 job I’m interested in per week (and apply)
  - Meet with at least 1 Turing colleague per week
  - Attend at least one tech conference, meet up, or hackathon each month
  - 1 Blog Post per week

#### Life:

  - At least one leisure activity per week
  - Take the dog on a walk at least three

### Strategy To Achieve Goals:
#### Coding:

  - Learn Linux, AWS, Python
  - Keep ruby current
  - Practice interview questions/algos

#### Professional Network:

  - Meet 2-4 new people in the field each week  (not related to looking for a job)
  - Identify 1 job I’m interested in per week (and apply)
  - Meet with at least 1 Turing colleague per week
  - Blog Post


